This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it discusses the energy consumption and coverage efficiency of small cell networks in 5G cellular networks. It may also belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category as it proposes an optimized energy density efficiency of hard core point process (HCPP) small cell networks. Additionally, it may belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category as it discusses the strategy for saving energy consumption in cellular networks. It may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as small cell networks are often used for multimedia applications. Finally, it may belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category as the switch-off strategy may have implications for network security.
